--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
plotMCMC 2.0-0 (2014-03-11)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
o Renamed package from "scapeMCMC" to "plotMCMC".

o Removed functions importMCMC() and importProj().

o Added arguments 'pch', 'cex', 'col', and 'sfrac' to plotQuant(style="bars").

o Added argument 'staplewex' to plotQuant(style="boxes").

o Changed default 'lty.median', 'lwd.median', 'col.outer', and 'boxwex' in
  plotQuant().

o Improved plotDens() to draw transparent posterior for fixed quantities.

o Added pch="." to plotSplom() examples, resulting in smaller package tarball.

o Simplified and renamed example objects so they are basic data frames: xpar
  (parameters), xrec (recruitment), xbio (biomass), and xpro (projections).




--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
scapeMCMC 1.1-3 (2011-09-29)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
o Improved plotQuant() and plotSplom() handling of 'mcmc' objects.




--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
scapeMCMC 1.1-2 (2011-02-09)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
o No user-visible changes.




--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
scapeMCMC 1.1-1 (2010-09-05)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
o Minor improvements in help pages.




--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
scapeMCMC 1.1-0 (2010-09-04)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
o Added argument 'col.strip' to plotDens() and plotTrace(), with gray as
  default.

o Changed default 'cex.axis' in plotDens() to 0.8.

o Reduced clutter at startup.

o Added two vignettes: dsc-vignette.pdf and gallery.pdf.

o Updated URLs and email address.




